		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=147660"><span id=>Tactikal</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />152 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.81]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Tactikal&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>You can drag your corpse as well as others and not break hide.&nbsp;&nbsp;You can move up to 3 corspes around at a time.  With the introduction of the /corpsedrag command it makes it much easier to corpse recover groups.  <br><br>I have that hotkeyed so as to make it easy.  Basically just make a hotkey and put /corpsedrag on line 1.  Using that you can drag 2 corpses without having to spam like you did before.  <br><br>But you can still also use the /corpse command to drag as well.  So make another hotkey for that as well.  <br><br>So you target a corpse hit you /corpsedrag hotkey, do another the same way.  Then you target the 3rd corpse and as you're running spam that hotkey as corpses dragged that way must be summoned relatively frequently in order to keep them in range.<br><br>Then you're going to need to make a hotkey to drop them.  The command is /corpsedrop.  Now if you have a corpse targeted then you will only drop that one.  But if you have no target at all you can drop all the corpses you are dragging.  Also note you don't need to /corpsedrop bodies you are draggin with /corpse.<br><br>Hope that makes sense to ya, if not tell me where I messed up and I'll try and go more into detail.<br><br>Almost forgot in order to be able to drag another persons corpse you have to get there consent.  All the person who needs the drag has to do is /consent &lt;yourname&gt;.  It also works with /consent group, /consent guild, and /consent raid.  Well those work if they are in the respective category you consented.<br><br>And on another note /consent group/guild/raid  DO NOT work if your bodies are popping out of an instanced zone.  You won't have to worry about this for some time I am sure.  But basically if the body zones then they have to consent individually AFTER the bodies pop into the newer zone.<br><br><br><i><span class="sm">Edited, Mon Nov 29 12:41:24 2004 by Tactikal</span class="sm"></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Infiltrator Kyppe Needsarez<br>70 Nemesis <br>Vazaelle<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1080830" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1080830</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
